        "job_description": "Full Stack Developer .Net C#\n\nApplication Developer Lead Analyst\n\nRole\n\nAs a .Net Full Stack Developer, you will be joining the Cigna technology team responsible for building and maintaining digital applications and services supporting our rapidly growing Middle East region.\n\nWorking as a member of an agile team, you’ll be responsible for supporting existing customized solutions in addition to developing new solutions, features and enhancements to support our Health Services business.\n\nWe are rapidly expanding the team to embark on a major change initiative to augment an existing application ecosystem to enable our business to expand into new markets in the MEA region and beyond. This is an exciting time to become part of the Cigna technology team, working on an initiative that is laying the foundations for our future state technology stack that will ultimately be used across our international business.\n\nAbout You\n\nYou’re an experienced Full Stack .Net developer with a strong track record of delivery and the desire to learn additional technical skills in complementary toolkits and packages.\n\nPassionate about all things technology and keep up to date with the latest industry trends and products.\n\nThe type of person that loves the challenge of solving complex technical problems by thinking outside the box.\n\nCore responsibilities:\n• Undertakes analysis, design and produces technical specification documentation for new development work and changes to existing applications.\n• Develops customised solutions leveraging the Microsoft .Net framework and utilizing ASP.Net, SQL, HTML, CSS, JavaScript and C#\n• Works as a member of an Agile Scrum team, delivering business value deployments in sprints of 2 weeks.\n• Acts a lead technical resource for .Net application related design, performance, security and configuration considerations.\n• Ensures that solutions adhere to software development best practices and security policies and control standards outlined in the Cigna Information Protection policy\n• Ensuring any developed solutions are written to be maintainable, scalable, testable and deployable.\n\nEssential:\n• Bachelor’s degree in Computer Sciences or equivalent or a related discipline\n• Minimum of 5 years' experience in supporting and developing .Net C# solutions in a production environment\n• Expert knowledge/experience in Asp.net web application / ASPX forms \n• Expert knowledge/experience in jQuery and Angular\n• Extensive knowledge/experience in oracle PL SQL and SQL\n• Good knowledge in React.Js, Node.js, Bootstrap.\n• Good knowledge in REST/SOAP standards.\n• Strong experience with Web services, WCF and Service Orientated Architecture\n• Excellent problem solving skills and a flair for reverse engineering complex code.\n• Comfortable working on a variety of tasks simultaneously with excellent organisational skills.\n• A passion for .Net and building scalable solutions\n\nDesirable:\n• Microsoft Certified.\n• Experience of using Microsoft Azure Devops or Jira\n• Experience of using Crystal Reports\n• Experience with Qlikview.\n• Experience gained within a financial services organization\n• Experience of mentoring and supporting other developers.\n• Experience working with Agile development methodologies\n\nCompetencies:\n• Flexible, open mind-set and comfortable working with existing systems.\n• Passionate about technology and applying it to business solutions.\n• Enthusiastic and possessing a “can do” attitude.\n• Have a track record of getting things done, within a fast-paced and changing environment.\n• Creative and be good at bringing others along with you.\n• Comfortable dealing with conflict.\n• You will be a team player with excellent written and oral communication skills.\n\nAbout The Cigna Group\n\nCigna Healthcare, a division of The Cigna Group, is an advocate for better health through every stage of life. We guide our customers through the health care system, empowering them with the information and insight they need to make the best choices for improving their health and vitality. Join us in driving growth and improving lives.",
