        "job_description": "Job Description:\n\nTruGolf is seeking a highly skilled and experienced Senior Unreal Engine 5 Developer to join our dynamic team. As a key member of our development group, you will play a crucial role in shaping the future of our virtual golf simulation products.\n\nResponsibilities:\n\n· Collaborate with the development team to create immersive and realistic virtual golf simulations.\n\n· Lead the development of high-quality, performant code for various game features, ensuring a seamless and immersive user experience using Unreal Engine 5.\n\n· Develop and maintain high-quality, efficient, and reusable code.\n\n· Offer technical consultation and assist team members with Unreal Engine based design and implementation patterns.\n\n· Utilize advanced blueprints in Unreal Engine 5 to create complex gameplay mechanics and systems.\n\n· Work closely with artists and designers to integrate visual and gameplay elements seamlessly.\n\n· Troubleshoot, optimize and debug code to resolve complex technical issues to ensure smooth gameplay and overall system performance.\n\n· Ensure that implementation of code, materials, and map setup is performant across multiple platforms, including mobile.\n\n· Stay updated on the latest industry trends, Unreal Engine updates, and emerging technologies.\n\n· Mentor and guide junior developers, fostering a collaborative and innovative work environment.\n\nRequirements:\n\n· Bachelor’s degree in computer science, Game Development, or related field (or equivalent work experience)\n\n· Near-supernatural understanding of Unreal Engine 5.\n\n· In-depth knowledge of Unreal Engine 5 rendering, networking, and optimization techniques.\n\n· Strong knowledge of C/C++ and object-oriented programming is mandatory.\n\n· Extensive experience with advanced blueprints in Unreal Engine 5.\n\n· Strong knowledge of modern mesh and shader optimization techniques.\n\n· Strong understanding of game development principles, graphics programming, and physics simulation.\n\n· Solid understanding of 3D math and graphics principles.\n\n· Experience working with Perforce, or similar version of source control.\n\n· Ability to work both independently and collaboratively in a team environment.\n\n· Strong communication skills and the ability to convey complex technical concepts to non-technical team members.\n\n· Passion for gaming and virtual reality experiences, especially in the sports simulation industry.\n\nDesired Skills and Bonus Points\n\n· A passion for golf or sports simulation is desirable.\n\n· Experience using Unity3D.\n\n· Familiarity with C# code.\n\n· Experience porting desktop games to mobile platforms.\n\n· Working knowledge of Agile, Scrum, and Kanban methodologies.\n\n· Has successfully shipped multiple titles across various desktop, console, and mobile platforms.\n\n· Mobile development experience with Unreal Engine, including iOS & Android. Console porting a plus.\n\nHow to Apply:\n\nPlease submit your resume and a cover letter detailing your relevant experience.\n\nIn your cover letter, include examples of your work, highlighting specific projects demonstrating your expertise in Unreal Engine development.\n\nTruGolf is an equal-opportunity employer and welcomes applicants from all backgrounds to apply. Join us in creating the future of virtual golf experiences!",
