        "job_description": "Current Employees:\n\nIf you are a current employee, please apply via the internal career site by logging into your Workday Account and clicking the Career icon on your homepage.\n\nStarting Pay Rate Range\n$45,468.80 - $56,825.60\n\n(Determined by the knowledge, skills, and experience of the applicant.)\n\nJob Summary\nThe Marketing and Public Relations Project Manager is responsible for routing marketing projects throughout the full life cycle. The Project Manager arranges and monitors movement of project request through development and the approval process; between all stakeholders including, project owner, creative, all final reviews and approvals. The Project Manager reviews and posts status on active projects in the marketing /creative development. The Project Manager also tracks and/or physically moves projects from one step of development/approval to the next. A project management tracking tool is used to track all movements and history of all projects.\n\nCandidates for this position must possess strong verbal and written communication skills, be deadline-driven and highly organized. Accuracy and an acute attention to detail are also critical to the role. Candidates must work well under pressure in a fast-paced environment, be able to multi-task and prioritize projects effectively, and possess excellent planning and problem-solving skills to be successful. This position requires a strong work ethic, self-motivation, confidence and the ability to work with different personalities as a team player. An understanding of creative process including design, copy, digital and print production is a plus, but not required.\n\nMonument Health offers competitive wages and benefits on qualifying positions. Some of those benefits can include:\n• Supportive work culture\n• Medical, Vision and Dental Coverage\n• Retirement Plans, Health Savings Account, and Flexible Spending Account\n• Instant pay is available for qualifying positions\n• Paid Time Off Accrual Bank\n• Opportunities for growth and advancement\n• Tuition assistance/reimbursement\n• Excellent pay differentials on qualifying positions (extra pay for working evening, nights or weekends)\n• Flexible scheduling\n\nJob Description\n\nEssential Functions:\n• Create or assist in the creation of multiple project plans and schedules.\n• Manage all incoming project requests.\n• Work closely with the Director of Marketing to help coordinate marketing campaigns and the needed creative assets.\n• Monitor the daily progress of projects.\n• Be proactive in meeting all deadlines, ensuring projects are sent for proof, released and approved on time.\n• Provide detailed updates to clients, team members or other stakeholders.\n• Ensure team members have the correct information they need to complete their assigned tasks on time.\n• Work efficiently through high volumes while meeting tight deadlines.\n• Take appropriate action if a deadline is not being met.\n• All other duties as assigned.\n\nAdditional Requirements\n\nRequired:\nEducation - Associates degree in Related Field\n\nPreferred:\nExperience - 2+ years of Project Management Experience\nPhysical Requirements:\nSedentary work - Exerting up to 10 pounds of force occasionally and/or negligible amount of force frequently or constantly to lift, carry, push, pull or otherwise move objects, including the human body. Sedentary work involves sitting most of the time.\n\nJob Category\nBusiness Administration\n\nJob Family\nMarketing and Communications\n\nDepartment\nCS PR/Marketing\n\nScheduled Weekly Hours\n40\n\nShift\n\nEmployee Type\nRegular\n15 Corporate Services Division\n\nMake a difference. Every day.\n\nMonument Health is an Equal Opportunity/Affirmative Action employer. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, national origin, disability, or protected Veteran status.",
