        "job_description": "Title: Python Developer\n\nLocation: Dallas Fort Worth, TX- will be more hybrid.\n\nLength: long-term - open-ended contract!\n\n5-6 yrs will work\n• This is a Python Automation Engineer/Python Developer type role - looking for automation skills with writing test scripts. Need to have robot framework, selenium, Wireshark and call flow exp. Any experience withing with 4G/5G, LET/VoLTE telecom domains.\n\nThe automation engineer at Telecommunication will work within a service development and maintenance engineering team responsible for writing scripts to test mobile voice and video services. Will be responsible for building and maintaining a library of automated tests to execute against the Telecommunication network, based on test plans provided by senior engineers. We are driving towards a zero-touch test environment.\n\nThe Position Requires\n\nMinimum of a BS degree in an engineering discipline is REQUIRED.\n\nMinimum of 2-4 years of overall programming experience is REQUIRED.\n\nMinimum of 2-4 years of overall testing experience is REQUIRED, PREFERRABLY in an automation environment.\n\nAt least 2 years of python programing experience in an automation environment is PREFERRED. Alternative languages include Perl, Groovy, Scala & JavaScript.\n\nSound understanding of programming and software concepts and principles including database, networking, json/xml, object oriented design is REQUIRED.\n\nAt least 2 years' experience of hands-on coding/scripting experience using Appium, Selenium, or a related mobile application automation framework (i.e. Perfecto Mobile) to test Android and iOS mobile applications is PREFERRED.\n\nFamiliarity with Testing Techniques and Methodologies - understanding of the various approaches used in testing, including white box (logic driven), black box (requirements driven), load testing, coverage testing and regression testing is REQUIRED.\n\nStrong Communication Skills (both Oral And Verbal) Are REQUIRED.\n\nAt least 1 year of Linux experience is REQUIRED.\n\nExperience with the Robot Framework for automated acceptance testing is DESIRED.\n\nKnowledge of and experience with IMS, SIP, VoIP and Video applications in a carrier/service provider/ISP environment is DESIRED.\n\nWorking knowledge of protocols, network technologies and standards including: 3GPP IMS-architecture, LTE, TCP/UDP, SIP, RTP, DNS, ENUM, GSMA-RCS, MMTel and other SIP/VoIP standards is DESIRED.\n\nExperience with debugging tools such as Wireshark and QXDM is DESIRED.\n\nKnowledge of other VoIP test, monitoring and debugging tools is DESIRED.\n\nPlease share resume at Career@tekintegral.com OR nkumar@tekintegral.com",
