        "job_description": "Software Tester*\n\nWiesbaden, Germany\n\nYour contribution\n\nIn this versatile role, you will be responsible for further customer-specific developments and adaptations of our software product portfolio in the diagnostic area. You will be part of an experienced team of software developers and testers, working on the creation of products to develop biotechnological and diagnostic applications in laboratory automation.\n• Design, generate and execute tests\n• Work in an interdisciplinary team on verification tasks\n• Troubleshoot issues and generate a path forward\n• Write clear and detailed technical speciﬁcations and documentation\n• Support the enhancement of functional and technical aspects of products and workflows\n• Work closely with the software development team to analyze issues and improve the software quality\n\nYour background\n\nWe're not just looking for hard skills: We're looking for people who bring their passion and talent to work.\n• A technical or scientific education; preferably biological, life science or software engineering\n• Several years of experience in software testing, preferably in the medical device industry\n• Experience in testing web and desktop applications\n• The ability to fluently speak and write English and preferable German\n• Preferably experience in Test Automation\n• Preferably an ISTQB certification (Foundation Level)\n\nWhat makes working at Tecan unique?\n• The chance to make it count and to have an impact on the world of tomorrow\n• Working in an international and diverse environment\n• The chance to grow your career within the company\n• Feel empowered by our strong and unique company culture\n• Comprehensive compensation and benefits package\n\nJoin Tecan, a great place to work! Read about our certification from Great Place to Work.\n\nWe're looking forward to receiving your application online. Please submit your CV or resume (w/o picture and w/o cover letter, reference letters and diplomas are optional).\n\nOnly applications that fully meet our requirements will be considered.\n\nFor questions, please contact Lena Weyers: lena.weyers@tecan.com\n• We welcome applications from people of all genders.\n\n#SoftwareVerification #Robotic #ISO13485 #Software #Softwaretest #QA #Verification #Testing #ISTQB #Agile\n\nOur purpose.\n\nAt Tecan we are driven to improve people's lives and health. We do this by empowering our customers to scale healthcare innovation globally from life science to the clinic. We collaborate with our customers from early-stage innovation through project implementation and beyond. We deliver the products, services and solutions that make lab processes and medical procedures precise, reproducible and compliant.\n\nStay unique and make it count.\n\nOur values - trust, highest standards and ambition - are the cornerstones of our business and provide the framework for Tecan's culture. We foster a positive and empowering environment where our rarest assets, our unique employees, can grow and bring their passion and talent to work.\n\nLegal entity: Tecan Software C.C. GmbH\n\nCity: Wiesbaden\n\nCountry: DE",
