        "job_description": "If you’re a multi-faceted IT professional with experience in UI/UX design and development of digital products AND you want to work from home, we’ve got an opportunity just for you!\n\nAt StandUp Wireless, we’re creating wireless solutions that reshape the industry, and we’re growing! We’re looking for a driven, collaborative UI/UX Designer/Developer to help us create and optimize internal tools to support critical operational processes.\n\nWho We Are\n\nStandUp Wireless is a wireless service provider focused on leveraging technical insights and innovative solutions to keep our communities connected. The company offers an energetic, entrepreneurial atmosphere where employees work in teams to help achieve goals. StandUp is a company built on trust that values individuals with personal initiative and creative solutions. We are a small but mighty company that makes a huge impact!\n\nWhat You’ll Be Doing\n\nAs UI/UX Designer/Developer, you will serve in a critical role, conceptualizing and building user-friendly and visually appealing interfaces for our customer experience, customer service, and other operational teams. The solutions you develop will influence the efficiency of our operational teams, making it easier for our employees to deliver better support to more customers. Your responsibilities will typically include:\n• Designing and developing digital user interfaces and user experiences using a variety of languages and tools.\n• Collaborating with stakeholders to identify and understand user interface needs; obtaining and responding to feedback throughout the development process.\n• Creating user personas, journey maps, and wireframes in the design process.\n• Planning and executing projects in accordance with specifications, budget, and timeline.\n• Continuously improving existing interfaces and incorporating new features to best meet users’ evolving needs.\n• Working closely with colleagues and cross functional teams to ensure design and development are aligned with stakeholder priorities and ensure product security.\n• Conducting usability testing, analyzing, and iterating products as needed.\n• Regularly reporting to supervisors and the senior management team on project progress.\n• Maintaining knowledge of emerging technologies and best practices in application design and development.\n\nHow You Qualify\n• Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Engineering or related field.\n• At least 5 years of experience in UI/UX design and development\n• Strategic thinker with a knack for problem-solving and innovation.\n• Effective collaborator with strong written, verbal, and visual communication skills.\n• Experience managing UI/UX projects.\n• Strong portfolio of effective, reliable, and secure UI/UX projects.\n• Talent for visual design and intuitive user-system interaction.\n• Ability to thrive in a fluid, fast-paced environment.\n\nWhat We Offer\n\nStandUp offers a culture that thrives by empowering our people and respecting everyone’s work-life balance. We work hard but have fun! Members of the StandUp Wireless family engage in a highly collaborative and fast paced environment that values their opinions in every step of the creative process.\n\nIn addition to the inviting culture and collaborative environment, StandUp Wireless offers great benefits:\n• Competitive Compensation\n• Bonus Incentive Programs\n• Medical, Dental and Vision Benefits Packages\n• 401K Plan\n• Company paid Life and Long-term Disability Benefits\n• Voluntary Benefits and Wellness Programs\n• Home Office Monthly Stipends\n• Paid vacation, sick leave and holidays.\n\nHow to Apply\n\nPLEASE SUBMIT RESUME AND DESIRED SALARY TO BE CONSIDERED FOR THIS ROLE\n\nCandidates must be legally eligible to work in the US for any employer.\n\nWe are an Equal Opportunity Employer that values diversity in the workplace.",
